<br>
 And a solar panel or radiator panel or antenna jams, and there's no chance of repairs, and the mission returns 1/100th of the originally planned science (if you're lucky) because of a bent $0.50 bolt.<br>
<br>
 Try to develop a robotic venture with the capability of an 8 man, 20 meter Orion expedition to Jupiter's moons (anything less won't fly because its too small &amp; risky). The versatility of the eye-brain circuit, with the ability to rig something which nobody in mission planning thought of a need for, to do an experiment that makes the entire mission more than worthwhile.<br>
<br>
 JPL did a study of robotic probes' abilities. They picked an interesting area of the Mohave, and did a complete survey to catalog all the clues about the history of the area. They next let a group of planetologists study the area at length -via robotics.<br>
